reviewText: Great course with a lot of information and real  time examples The only but important disadvantage at least for me is that  I have completed the course 6 days ago and submitted all the necessary exercises/assignments and still waiting for 1 assignment to be revied and graded although I leave comments every day in order someone to review it (a lot of views but not reviews).So I am still waiting for the grade of 1 exercice in order to complete the specialization. I think that the course should be more organized and not leave the reviewing/grading on others candidates  disposal - availability after a period as in this case I am waiting with no reason.
More Content with Exemplars are required and more rigour in the assignments should be incorporated to complete this course.
Es bueno, sin embargo las evaluaciones están a cargo de compañeros, lo cual hace un poco más tardada la conclusión del curso.

Well structured courses but the capstone for the final week requires participantion of peers via private meetings which make this part very difficult to finalize and time consuming. In addition the teachers could have used better presentations and exmples instead of just talking about the content, it was sometimes quite boring to follow,
A good introductory course. A bit difficult to find partners for the capstone project.

The elements of passive listening, repetition, active submission of assignments and interaction with peers was a major plus of this course and inspiring to do more of this kind of learning. Thank you Prof. Colson and your team!
